{"id": "duc04-testb-26:4#13", "contents": "Tony Leon, the head of the Democratic Party, has expressed his strong opposition to the proposed amnesty, arguing that it would only serve to reward those who engaged in thuglike behavior during the apartheid era. \"The more thuglike your behavior, the more you get away with,\" he says, highlighting his concerns that a new amnesty would undermine the principles of justice and accountability. Despite his party's opposition, Leon acknowledges that his is a lonely voice in the current political climate."}
